definitions.definition: A fine ; a fee or monetary penalty incurred for breaking the law; usually for a minor offence such as a traffic violation .
examples: You better pay off the parking summon tomorrow before you kena interest on it.

definitions.definition: A notice of an infringement of the law, usually incurring such a penalty; a citation or ticket .
